    • Eion P.
      Ambler, PA
      7 Italian Food reviews
      Sep 9, 2025
      3 photos

      The BEST meal I've had in Cleveland!

      Moved here a couple of months ago and am still new to the food scene. Heard about this place through a coworker (who said it was the best spot in Little Italy).

      We ordered the honey and ricotta bread course...still thinking about that dish...the bread was buttery, garlicky, SOFT yet crispy. The whipped ricotta was insanely delicious. We split the ragu, frutti di mare, and scallops. The scallops were 10/10 best bite of the night. Ragu was fantastic. That sauce tasted like it had been simmering for hours. The frutti di mare was OK (not sure if squid ink pasta is my thing yet), but the sauce had a nice spice and a bold, seafood-forward flavor.

      Portions were so generous and pricing was honestly fair for this 2025 economy. The ambience was classic, no-fuss Italian fare: white tablecloths, Frank Sinatra , humble staff. And best part is it felt fancy and yet no one would judge you for wearing whatever you wanted.

      Mia Bella is no-frills, fantastic Italian cooking. We will be back...and back...many times.

      Went to dinner with friends Saturday 6/21. Had reservations but we arrived early. Checked with hostess and she said she would see if she could get us in early, which we appreciated. Left phone number and walked the area. 15 mins git a call and we got seated 45 mins ahead of reservation! Thank you very much.
      Now the VERY disappoiting part of the evening. When the server, Gizem came to our table, W3, she first asked if we wanted water or sparkling water. We elected sparkling water. Took the appetizer and drink order and left. Came back with two bottles of sparkling water and then took the dinner orders. I chose the Cheese Tortellini and my wife asked about the Short Rib Bolognese. Server asked my wife if she wanted the Ragu, which was much better. My wife said yes, not knowing it was a completely different dish, which the server never explained. Not only that, the server did not state the specials nor their respective costs. Also our dinner partners also had the same selections on sparkling water and the Short Rib Bolognese, then Ragu changes.
      The dishes were excellent, served hot and quickly after placing orders.
      Finished and received our bills! With the server NOT TELLING each of us the additional costs for sparkling waters and two RAGU dishes instead of the original plates of Short Rib Bolognese, this server inflated each bill by $30!!! No $30 will not break me, but the way the padding of the dishes, is and was, highly deceptive. This does not present Mia Bella in a good light for future visits or recommendations.AND I'm not even going in on charging me a processing fee for using my credit card!!

      Jun 29, 2024Previous review

      Our anniversary dinner plans were impacted by the weather, so we had to do something else. Called and was able to get reservations for four early in the day, for a Saturday night. And were we pleasantly surprised! First the weather changed and we were able to eat outside! A beautiful evening started our nite.

      We were treated by our server Yassline! (More about him later) Our drink orders were taken right after we were told of the specials. Placed our orders and within minutes our drinks appeared! Then came the salads, without haste! Since it was a warm evening, our water glasses were attended without any request! Well done staff!!

      Then our meals. Two orders of Cheese Tortellini; an order of Cheese Ravioli; and one order of spaghetti. Within a very short time, all of our dishes were served, each one piping hot, just as one would hope! The serving was delightful, but the taste.....Fantastic! We normally love to converse over our plates..not tonight! No one wanted to stop the process of eating such wonderful dishes. You can say these were simple, basic Italian plates. True, but these stood out and pretty much matched such plates we enjoyed last year in Florence Italy. Cannot express how wonderful each dish was. To top it off, we shared the "Cookie and Gelato" desert. A thick, warm chocolate chip cookie, along side a scoop of French vanilla gelato, was a perfect closing to our anniversary dinner.

      Now our server, Yassline! This young man was on top of everything! Made suggestions for dishes; joy fully answer any question presented. Returned many times to check on us, without seeming intrusive! He said how he started at Mia Bella and how HE wanted to create a serving manner that was both informative and enjoyable to the customer! One of the best servers I have come across in my decades of dining. If you happen to get him, you will know what I mean. Many thanks, Yassline!!

      Feb 7, 2016Previous review

      After taking in the Orchid Mania at the Cleveland Botanical Gardens, we were looking for a nice quiet spot to have an early Sunday dinner. After searching the Yelp app, Mia Bella sounded like the perfect place. And we were not disappointed at all!!

      A short drive up Mayfield Rd from the Gardens, this corner road restaurant was perfect! Not crowded but various patrons were enjoying the pleasant surroundings. (A couple sitting behind us happened to be the same couple who asked me to take their picture in front of an Orchid display earlier, so they too picked a great spot.)

      After being seated and given both the wine list and menu, we were promptly attended to by our server who gave us the time we needed to review the delights, since this was out first visit. Our pre-meal drinks and fresh bread/butter were delivered as we made out decisions! On a rare occasion we both picked the same dish albeit slightly altered. My wife picked the ravioli, stuffed with cheese, while I altered mine to be veal stuffed.

      Both dishes arrived quickly and heated to our liking, hot! (How many times do you order a dish and no matter what the time, it arrives at a temp not to your liking? Won't happen here!) In addition to the stuffed ravioli, the dish also contained fried artichoke! Now you mush know I am not a fan of this item but I now am!! What a delight to the dish. Overall the plates were wonderful and highly recommended.

      Since we both skipped breakfast, we indulged in desert! Okay we split it but it was a perfect ending, Bailey Gelato. Two scoops, one for each was a perfect way to end the meal.

      If you have not visited Mia Bella all I can say is, "Get a move on it and get there!" A true diamond among many on "The Hill"!

      Candace was our excellent server and she couldn't have been more helpful. She knew the menu and asked the right questions to hone in on what she thought we would like. Five stars!
      We started with the burratta salad which was so yummy. Then we shared the Chef's Favorite pizza which was cooked perfectly and had a subtle little kick to it. Next we shared a fantastic chicken piccata which Candace had the chef make with boneless chicken breast. We topped all that off with a creme brûlée that was the best we've ever had. The only thing I would change is the location of the table which was in a very high traffic spot next to the bar. Otherwise 5 stars!
